&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategize&lt;/strong&gt;, plan, write, manage internal and external contributors and review region specific investigational stage CMC summary submission documents (Module 2, Module 3, IMPD, etc.) and agency requests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deliver &lt;/strong&gt;high quality regulatory US, EU and ROW submissions, strategy and advice.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support&lt;/strong&gt; review of investigational product labels, protocols, investigator’s brochure, and other clinical trial materials; GMP inspections as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assess and identify&lt;/strong&gt; on an ongoing basis, risk mitigation plans based on current and changing US and Ex-US GMP regulations and guidance.&lt;/li&gt;
